%% Diagram: Edge compute request lifecycle — isolate warmed during TLS handshake
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant Client
    participant Edge as Edge PoP\n(TLS terminator)
    participant Iso as Worker runtime\n(V8 isolate / Wasm sandbox)
    participant Cache as Edge cache
    participant Origin

    Client->>Edge: TCP / QUIC connect
    Client->>Edge: TLS ClientHello (SNI = app.example.com)
    Note over Edge: Read SNI, identify worker\nfor this hostname
    par TLS handshake completes
        Edge-->>Client: ServerHello, certificate
    and Pre-warm worker
        Edge->>Iso: Instantiate isolate /\nWasm module (single-digit ms)
    end
    Note over Edge,Iso: First request observes ~0 ms cold start\n(work hidden behind TLS RTT)

    Client->>Edge: HTTP request
    Edge->>Iso: Dispatch fetch event
    Iso->>Cache: cache.match(req)
    alt Hit
        Cache-->>Iso: Response
    else Miss
        Iso->>Origin: subrequest (or KV / D1 / Durable Object)
        Origin-->>Iso: Response
        Iso->>Cache: cache.put(req, resp)
    end
    Iso-->>Edge: Response (mutated headers, body)
    Edge-->>Client: HTTP response over the same connection
